Category: Energy
name: Installation, maintenance and repair of instruments and devices for measuring, regulation and controlling energy performance of buildings.


Questions 1:

<h4>
    You start the assessment for an activity of the type: Installation, Maintenance And Repair
     Of Instruments And Devices For Measuring, Regulation And Controlling Energy Performance Of Buildings
</h4>

<h4>
    Please note that you must complete this assessment for each instrument/device individually, as both component-specific and 
    location-specific information is required. The activity therefore relates to a 
    single instrument/device. If you have several instrument/device, please carry out this assessment several times.
</h4>

<p>
    Instructions for the assessment:
</p>

<ul>
    <li>All input will be saved automatically</li>
    <li>While doing the assessment you can go back and forth to the different questions at any time</li>
    <li>Evaluation dashboard will be created after you actively finish the assessment by clicking the respective button</li>
</ul>


Questions 2:


<h4>
    Your company installs, maintains, and repairs of instruments and devices for measuring, regulating, and controlling 
    energy performance of buildings. The economic activities in this category could be associated with NACE codes F42, 
    F43, M71, C16, C17, C22, C23, C25, C27, C28.
</h4>

<h5>
    The company must perform at least one of these measures to ensure that the activity fulfills the substantial contribution criteria:
</h5>

<ul>
    <li>Installation, maintenance and repair of zoned thermostats, smart thermostat systems and sensing equipment, including motion and day light control</li>
    <li>Installation, maintenance and repair of building automation and 
        control systems, building energy management systems (BEMS), lighting control systems and energy management systems (EMS)</li>
    <li>Installation, maintenance and repair of smart meters for gas, heat, cool and electricity</li>
    <li>Installation, maintenance and repair of fa√ßade and roofing elements with a solar shading or 
        solar control function, including those that support the growing of vegetation</li>
</ul>

<p>
    Certification: <br>
    <i>If you want to get certified, we need proof that your company performs the activity you selected. 
        Please provide a short description (4-8 sentences) of the economic activity your company performs. 
        This description allows the certifier to clearly understand whether the activity is Taxonomy-eligible. 
        Please also upload a document that specifies the type of activity performed and clearly ties it to your company.</i>
</p>

<ul>
    <li>Government-issued registration documents & licenses</li>
    <li>Financial statements and reports</li>
    <li>Project contracts and agreements</li>
    <li>Invoices for the performed activity</li>
</ul>





